    • Field Detail

      • id

        public final long id
        ID of the media expressed as a 64-bit integer.

      • idStr

        public final String idStr
        ID of the media expressed as a string.

      • mediaUrl

        public final String mediaUrl
        A http:// URL pointing directly to the uploaded media file. For media in direct messages, media_url is the same https URL as media_url_https and must be accessed via an authenticated twitter.com session or by signing a request with the user's access token using OAuth 1.0A. It is not possible to directly embed these images in a web page.

      • mediaUrlHttps

        public final String mediaUrlHttps
        A https:// URL pointing directly to the uploaded media file, for embedding on https pages. For media in direct messages, media_url_https must be accessed via an authenticated twitter.com session or by signing a request with the user's access token using OAuth 1.0A. It is not possible to directly embed these images in a web page.

      • sizes

        public final MediaEntity.Sizes sizes
        An object showing available sizes for the media file.

      • sourceStatusId

        public final long sourceStatusId
        For Tweets containing media that was originally associated with a different tweet, this ID points to the original Tweet.

      • sourceStatusIdStr

        public final String sourceStatusIdStr
        For Tweets containing media that was originally associated with a different tweet, this string-based ID points to the original Tweet.

      • type

        public final String type
        Type of uploaded media.

      • videoInfo

        public final VideoInfo videoInfo
        An object showing details for the video file. This field is present only when there is a video in the payload.

      • indices

        public final List<Integer> indices
        An array of integers indicating the offsets.
